title: [BUG] Unsupported CONFIG parameter: appendfilename
body:
When I run `CONFIG GET *`, there is key `appendfilename` on the response.

But when I want to run `CONFIG SET appendfilename something` it says
```
-ERR Unsupported CONFIG parameter: appendfilename
```
**Additional information**
I am using docker image redis:alpine and redis:latest.

comments_data.body: This specific config is immutable, it can only be modified at startup time (in the config file or command line arguments)
